  "prompt": "How do I reduce lips protrusion without surgery?",
  "response": "Reducing lip protrusion without surgery can involve several non-invasive approaches. Here are some options to consider:\n\n1. **Dermal Fillers**: While typically used to enhance lips, in some cases, fillers can be strategically used to balance the shape of the lips and create a more proportional appearance.\n\n2. **Lip Exercises**: Certain exercises may help tone the muscles around the lips. These exercises can involve puckering, stretching, and other movements designed to enhance lip control.\n\n3. **Makeup Techniques**: Contouring and specific makeup techniques can create the illusion of less protruding lips. Using darker shades around the lips or a specific lip-lining technique can alter the perceived shape.\n\n4. **Facial Aesthetics**: Consulting with a specialist in facial aesthetics may provide insight into treatments such as Botox, which can relax certain muscles in the face and potentially reduce the appearance of lip protrusion.\n\n5. **Weight Management**: Sometimes, overall body weight can affect facial features. Maintaining a healthy weight through diet and exercise may subtly affect the appearance of your lips.\n\n6. **Avoiding Certain Foods**: Reducing salt intake can decrease fluid retention and swelling in the lips, which may help make them appear less protruding.\n\n7. **Hydration**: Staying well-hydrated can help maintain skin elasticity and overall facial appearance.\n\n8. **Consultation with Professionals**: A consultation with a dentist or orthodontist may provide options such as braces or aligners, especially if the protrusion is related to dental alignment.\n\nRemember to consult with a qualified professional before pursuing any treatment options, as they can assess your specific situation and provide personalized recommendations.",
